hat I saw, but fairly expresses\nmy feeling. I had expected something pretty good, because I have consid\nerable faith in your agents, whom 1 happen to know; but what I saw is far\nbeyond my expectation.\ndrove hurriedly over probably twenty-five miles of ground, passing sev\neral of your flowing wells and tanks, and I don't believe that there ia aa\nacre of grotrnd that is not fit for first-class cultivation.\nUpon my return to Little Rock I shall take out several more share\nbefore they are gone, and will advise my friends all to take as many as they\ncan afford.\nI have just written to my brother in Indiana, advising him to do this oik\nmy judgment.\nI certainly think your proposition is one of the most liberal proposition\n.1 have ever seen offered, and I certainly think that the people of South Texas\nwill owe to you an everlasting debt of gratitude for the method you are\nusing to settle this veritable garden of Eden with new people.\nI thank you for the courtesies extended ,me on my recent visit, and I\ntrust the time will not be long when the division will occur, and I certainly\nshall return to Little Rock figuring on eventually coming hack to Atascosa\nCounty. Yours very truly, E. A. KINGSLEY,\nCity Engineer, Little Rock, Ark.\nWrite today for full particulars and photograph! allowing views on the ranch\nDR. CHAS. F.\n215 Alamo Plaza.\natlMslR oe-TMCraaaiLV.\nkin, ova, svomcn, Miaacs and childrcn.\nt f M fMsjr aw feet naausuaxsravw im\nf.L0irltMiDd$5 GDlEioCimotBeLiuilleilAliUrPrlcsj\n-f yA CTIOW. W t. Ponslas naras and arles Is stamp! en bottoo. 1\n.tod Brio\naasMOasak ass. ss aq sett\nNHN MaOIOALCO,\nf S 1\nMLEs K0 money till com-kzz\nIT JasaWsa-&ey TWOTpel j HHSOQ- 0a 3T. (UKVO QT\natMtofcsKssiMjSuCaaw. MOMRQE\nMourite\nSkin Soap\nWarm baths with Cuticura\nSoap followed.-when neces\nsary, by gentle anointings\nwith Cuticura, the great\nSkin Cure, preserve, purify\nand beautify the skin, scalp,\nhair and hands of infants\nand children, relieve ecze\nmas,